**Product 1 Image Display using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**
===========================================================

In this example, we will create a simple web page that displays the product 1 image using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. We will also use Core PHP to handle the backend logic and MySQL/MariaDB as our database.

**Database Schema**
-------------------

First, let's create a simple database schema to store our product information.

```sql
CREATE TABLE products (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  image_url VARCHAR(255)
);
```

**PHP Backend Logic**
---------------------

Next, let's create a PHP script that will handle the backend logic for our application.

```php
// config.php
<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "root";
$password = "";
$dbname = "mydatabase";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
  die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}

// Get product 1 image
$product_id = 1;
$sql = "SELECT image_url FROM products WHERE id = '$product_id'";
$result = $conn->query($sql);

if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
  // Output data of each row
  while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
    $image_url = $row["image_url"];
  }
} else {
  $image_url = "";
}

$conn->close();
?>
```

**HTML and CSS**
----------------

Now, let's create the HTML and CSS for our web page.

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Product 1 Image</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="product-image">
    <img id="product-image" src="" alt="Product 1 Image">
  </div>

  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

```css
/* style.css */
.product-image {
  width: 50%;
  margin: 40px auto;
  text-align: center;
}

#product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  border-radius: 10px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}
```

**JavaScript**
--------------

Finally, let's add the JavaScript code that will display the product 1 image.

```javascript
// script.js
fetch('config.php')
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => {
    const productImage = document.getElementById('product-image');
    productImage.src = data.image_url;
  })
  .catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
```

However, since we are using PHP to get the image URL, we need to modify the JavaScript code to make an AJAX request to the PHP script.

```javascript
// script.js
const xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open('GET', 'config.php', true);
xhr.onload = function() {
  if (xhr.status === 200) {
    const productImage = document.getElementById('product-image');
    productImage.src = xhr.responseText;
  }
};
xhr.send();
```

And we need to modify the PHP script to output the image URL.

```php
// config.php
<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "root";
$password = "";
$dbname = "mydatabase";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
  die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}

// Get product 1 image
$product_id = 1;
$sql = "SELECT image_url FROM products WHERE id = '$product_id'";
$result = $conn->query($sql);

if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
  // Output data of each row
  while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
    $image_url = $row["image_url"];
    echo $image_url;
  }
} else {
  echo "";
}

$conn->close();
?>
```

**Full Code**
-------------

Here is the full code for the example.

### config.php
```php
<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "root";
$password = "";
$dbname = "mydatabase";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
  die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}

// Get product 1 image
$product_id = 1;
$sql = "SELECT image_url FROM products WHERE id = '$product_id'";
$result = $conn->query($sql);

if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
  // Output data of each row
  while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
    $image_url = $row["image_url"];
    echo $image_url;
  }
} else {
  echo "";
}

$conn->close();
?>
```

### index.html
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Product 1 Image</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="product-image">
    <img id="product-image" src="" alt="Product 1 Image">
  </div>

  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### style.css
```css
.product-image {
  width: 50%;
  margin: 40px auto;
  text-align: center;
}

#product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  border-radius: 10px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}
```

### script.js
```javascript
const xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
xhr.open('GET', 'config.php', true);
xhr.onload = function() {
  if (xhr.status === 200) {
    const productImage = document.getElementById('product-image');
    productImage.src = xhr.responseText;
  }
};
xhr.send();
```

Note: Make sure to replace the database credentials and the image URL with your own values. Also, this is a basic example and you should consider security measures such as validating user input and using prepared statements to prevent SQL injection.